to create a package.json file:
npm init

to create one with default values:
npm init -y

list all packages installed in project:
npm list

show all versions of a package:
npm view package-name versions

install the latest major version of a package
npm install package-name@latest

install a minor version
npm install package-name@^2.2

install a patch version
npm install package-name@~2.2


the package lock json file will install everything to exactly what the authors used (versions)

creates a lockfile for exact packages (not automatic):
npm shrinkwrap

remove a package but leave it in the json:
npm uninstall package

remove the package from the json file:
npm uninstall package --save

save something as a dev dependency:
npm install package --save-dev